node.text: UPDATE: goldfish were returned! I was told these wouldn’t get large and when I brought them back I was told by another person that the first guy was wrong hahahaha. Thanks for the tips yall. Added some beneficial substrate for the plants and replaced them with a small scoop of tetras. A little experiment in propagation. I feed the fish, the fish shit out their butts and the roots are tickled with fecal joy and in return, so am I.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tyler Thrasher on August 14, 2021.

node.text:
I just got word back that we won’t be able to up the quantity of the Phantom Flora in time! This book is so intensive to make that we won’t be able to get more printing until early 2022 and they won’t be available until early summer that year! Which means the remaining 900 that remain are all we’ll have available until then. Just a heads up for anyone eyeballing this new journal! 
#phantomflora #flowerpressing #vellum #tylerthrasher #sketchbook

node.text:
I believe there aren’t black thumbs. Just those who aren’t taking good notes. I’ve set out to do what no Pinterest post or DIY plant blog has done, encourage you to learn on your own with a simple method for documenting YOUR observations. There is not one single way to grow plants and this journal reflects that. It’s tailored to your collection, your needs and most importantly your mistakes, which come as the most valuable asset when learning to grow. The Grow a Damn journal comes with 100 entry pages for your plants, a table of contents to find your entries easily, tips on fertilizer, pH, soil amendments, pests and more! As well as a garden planning or greenhouse planning fold out page. With over 8,000 copies already sold I’m not slowing down. Not until we’ve sold a copy for every plant murdering Pinterest post (I’ll be here a while.) You can order your copy of the Grow a Damn journal directly from the shop link in my bio!
#growadamn #plantjournal #learn #botany #science #citizenscientist

node.text:
Scenario time! You stumble upon a magical lamp with a genie inside who specializes in returned or refunded wishes. He tells you he runs the goodwill of wishes and you can have one for free, buts it’s a blind bag. You have no idea what wish you’ll get. The genie says there’s no real catch except for the blind grab aspect. He’s just trying to clear out some inventory. You can assume the people who made the wishes were well intentioned. They made these wishes with the intent to better their lives but returned them for unknown reasons. None of the initial wishes were made to trick others down the line. The last thing, you aren’t allowed to return the wish when you take it. No double returns. Will you take a blind wish! Why or why not?
#sceneriotime #storytelling #questionsforyou #whatwouldyoudo

node.text:
Crystallizing beetles is tricky but incredibly rewarding. Usually the elytra is too smooth for crystals to nucleate on to, leaving the abdomen and the rim of the elytra as the main growth points. Beetles usually take several batches, but once crystals adhere to the body they turn into these little abdomen geodes. The other trick is keeping crystals from forming too heavily on the wings so they don’t tear. 
#crystallized #chemistry #science #art #crystals #beetle #insects

node.text:
The routine for watering my variegated Monstera collection? Pull up a 5 gallon bucket of rain water and dunk those mothereffers one at a time. I add plenty of pumice and orchid bark to my Monstera mix so I’m never worried about overwatering. This dunk method also helps to disturb the soil as water rushes up from below, allowing air to gurgle into the pot and ensures the entire root system gets access to moisture.
#plants #planttips #planthelp #monstera #wateringtips
